What artist are promising for art invesments?

Insights from analyising data from over 220,000 art pieces

On my data-driven Artventure of investing in art I started analysing data to gain insights about the art ecosystem. Therefore, I have been scraping data from a website called ExpressoBeans, which is an art collectors community maintained by volunteers. It is an excellent start for public available data about art pieces.

From the website I could get gather data from over 220,000 art pieces. The data set contains different features of interest:

Class

The class feature describes what kind of art the artwork is. There are 27 classes available, however about 90% are Posters, Art Prints or Original Art.

Around 88% of all art pieces are Posters, Print Art and Original Art. I wrote in my article A Cost Effecti

Release Date

I visualized the number of art pieces for different release year buckets. Almost 80% of all the art pieces were released between 1992 and 2021. Although the oldest art piece was from 1662, you can say the expressobeans data set is modern art data set.

Status

Almost 90% of the art in the data set is official, 5% is fan art created by fans of artists, musicians, an author or somthing similar.

To get an idea what Fan Art is the piece Phish Englewood CO 00 Everett - 1st from Michael Everett which average selling price was $2537.5.
